This paper deals with the analysis of a wireless network utilizing energy harvesting technology, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication in computer science. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of throughput and stability, which are related to information theory and mathematical analysis, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of numerical simulations, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
